rComments: I had him in two classes and both were asynchronous. They were both in the same format. slides don't have a lot of information and so you do need to listen well and take notes of what he is saying. Lots of information but his class isn't hard if you do the work needed.

All I can say is that I regret taking a class with this professor. There are only 3 assessments that are worth a lot so if you slip up, it'll be hard to get back on track. He was TERRIBLE at replying to emails and when he did, he was condescending and unhelpful. Overall, I was excited to take this course but genuinely disappointed by the prof

Professor Landriault is by far the best professor I've had. His lectures are very interesting and engaging. He clearly cares about his students and his feedback is very helpful. I must admit I was reluctant to take a class with him because of some negative reviews but I can assure you that he's a fantastic prof. Overall, I learned a lot.

Honestly, the best professor I've had in the field of political science yet. He was kind and engaging to listen to, and great to answer questions outside of class time. His lectures are clear and concise, as are his expectations for you as a student. There isn't a lot on the slides, but if you attend lectures regularly it won't be an issue!
proffessor that thinks that writting 30 pages of one subject eill make you learn better

It's not an easy class but... don't expect anything less since it's 3rd year. He is tough grader but I've learned quite a bit (things that will be useful for other classes). 3 points: mid-term (25%), 12-15 pages research (40%) and a final (35%). Pay attention and take notes. Attendance is mandatory (PowerPoint slides are bare bone).

He's such a nice professor, always smiling and engaging with the class. Makes funny jokes a well, definitely a pleasure to listen to. Yes, his PowerPoint slides contain basically nothing, but if you show up for class and take notes, you'll be fine. Just drop in the key terms that he mentions in class and it's easy marks. Start early on the essay!

His PowerPoints barely contain anything, so you need to attend class even though they are posted online. I liked that he illustred every concept with a concrete example. He was very severe when grading the midterm exam, but not so much when it came to our research essay and final exam.

M. Landriault était très souriant et il engageait la discussion avec les étudiants en classe. Par contre, il était très sévère dans la correction de ses examens. Il recherche une très grande précision dans les analyses. Dans ce cours, il y avait un examen de mi-session (25%), un travail de recherche (40%) et un examen final non-cumulatif (35%).

Mathieu Landriault can't speak english. His power points are half french half english. When you ask a question, his answer is: "you should know it", not very helpful. The subject of his class is interesting, but he makes it boring. Not a very good class.

Un peu lent comme prof, pas tres clair quand c'est interactif, tres personnel sur certains sujets... Pour exam il donne quoi reviser les definition et tout ca. En gros un peu bizarre, si sa matiere n'etait pas bien je serai deja morte je crois. Mais ce qui est bien c'est qu'on retrouve les videos sur blackboard!!!

he s not that bad for a teacher-took the class as a summer class and the class was pretty interesting-u have to participate in order to get point for participation-exams weren't that hard-just had to know the subject and then write what you know about it
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Jai adore ce prof, il est tough pour donner des notes mais faut seulement ecrire plus de ce quil demande pis ca va etre correct. Il donne beaucoup de place pour participer, il engage le monde et cest vrm super fun. Il donne bcp de devoirs!!!

This Professor's expectations regarding assignments are exceptionally unclear, verging on the edge of contradicting his own course outline. Has clear favourites within the seminar. Avoid at all costs.

Great prof if you're willing to engage with the material. Course is relatively dry, but he makes electoral politics quite fun and interesting. Assignment requirements are quite vague which can make things confusing, but go talk to him and he can guide you along. Very approachable and personable despite not appearing so.
This Prof is bad. Does not care about his students class lectures are boring. expectations on assignments are not clear.

Great Prof. Don't understand the negative reviews, he made a difficult subject extremely easy to understand and was always willing to clarify further. The fact you must take notes and attend class should not be a fault of the the prof. this is university after all. Very interesting prof and textbook is merely to supplement the lectures.
His lectures are dull, and some of the material he conveys is questionable. He doesn't seem to be very open-minded to alternative opinions in class. If you can choose another professor, do so.

You HAVE to attend class because all the material is in his lecture (not his slides) but he is very straight forward, nice and clear. He really encourages students to think about all sides of an issue and the material is interesting. He brings in speakers and there are DGDs that help to further clear things up. Clear expectations & pretty fair exam

Very dull character, mono-tone voice. Slides were useless. Attending class is a must. Slides were simply a title with no content.  Fairly rude. Loved this subject hated the class.  I suggest taking a different course, even if you love the subject like i did. Pretty disappointing and upsetting class.

This prof is incredible. He makes a very complicated topic very easy to understand. His power points have very little on them,which is why it's important to pay attention. He is also a very easy marker. Take this course if you're interested in anything political related.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS. This guy has no idea what he's talking about. His slides are useless, they simply have the title of each topic, with no info. His lectures are boring. His expectations are not clear, and he is very unreasonable. I was sick and hospitalized for a week, brought him a doctor's note and he still wouldn't give me and extension...
